            "summary": "BOOKS I'M READING Learning, like Design is never complete. Here are some&hellip;",
            "content_html": "<h2>BOOKS I'M READING</h2>\n<p>Learning, like Design is never complete. Here are some of the books that have inspired me and helped me shape my thinking as a designer.</p>\n<figure class=\"post__image\"><img loading=\"lazy\"  src=\"https://kaihouse.github.io/media/posts/10/about-face.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" srcset=\"https://kaihouse.github.io/media/posts/10/responsive/about-face-xs.jpg 300w ,https://kaihouse.github.io/media/posts/10/responsive/about-face-sm.jpg 480w ,https://kaihouse.github.io/media/posts/10/responsive/about-face-md.jpg 768w ,https://kaihouse.github.io/media/posts/10/responsive/about-face-lg.jpg 1024w\"  alt=\"\" width=\"398\" height=\"500\"></figure>\n<p><span style=\"letter-spacing: -0.0111111rem; color: var(--headings-color); font-family: var(--font-base); font-size: 1.125em; font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);\">“Design is a funny word. Some people think design means how it looks. But of course, if you dig deeper, it’s really how it works.”</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.0555556rem; font-size: 0.666667rem; text-align: center; color: var(--text-editor-body-color); font-family: var(--font-base); font-weight: var(--font-weight-normal);\">– STEVE JOBS</span></p>",
